The holidays aren't open everywhere
In Hungary, the days are well-established by law and it has become common practice to move working days around the holidays, which is expected less times next year.
There are no uniform holidays in the European Union or in America.
The Hungarian legal system distinguishes between national and national holidays and days of rest at work.
The days of work are usually related to church holidays or important historical events.
We also celebrate the New Year: the last day of the old and the first day of the new year is off work - for the New Year so that people can rest after New Year's Eve.
In the course of the year, we have 11 free holidays in total.
The national festival is the 15th of March celebrating the revolution of 1848 and 23 October, the commemorative day of the revolution of 1956.
On August 20, we celebrate the founding of the state, May 1st, work, November 1st and 2nd, we remember dead relatives and friends.
Besides, it's two days of Easter, Pentecost and Christmas.
