What insurance is suitable for me?
Car insurance, which protects drivers in the event of an accident, is a significant expenditure that depends on different factors such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of a driving licence, type of vehicle to be insured or used, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
It is even more difficult to choose a suitable car insurance than to choose a car model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we're talking about.
The car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured person.
This obligation shall take the form of an insurance contract which provides that the insurance undertaking shall receive an agreed amount of insurance for taking charge of the payment of the damage in the event of an insurance event.
Insurance is the price of insurance to be determined taking into account different factors such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of a driving licence, type of vehicle that is insured or used, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so the higher the probability of a crash, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both those aged 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, insurance companies came to the conclusion that married persons have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of the journey and thus the probability that it will have an accident.
The increase in driving frequency increases the likelihood.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when determining the price of insurance.
The driver must therefore carefully examine the situation in order to choose the insurance best suited to his insurance profile.
We will show the most important variables for the choice of one or the same type of insurance, which, in addition to satisfying the type of insurer, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of 25 face different disadvantages, such as little experience in driving and short possession of a driving licence when they want to make an insurance claim at an affordable price.
Although the insurance against all risks is ideal for good coverage, there are even cheaper variants.
The most careful drivers can choose insurance against all risks with an insurance discount in order to obtain insurance cover for all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would assume the participation of the client in the payment of the insurance event.
"The part of the payment of the insurance event provided by the client will be determined in advance when determining the premium price, which will be the higher the lower the participation", explains Luis Noguera, head of First Europe in Spain, internet insurance intermediary.
Another option is the insurance extended to other participants in the operation by insuring the client against the damage caused to others, but not against the damage to his own car.
In addition, he would be insured against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
Recommendations.
If you are under twenty-five years old, try to be considerate and avoid accidents as much as possible, since it will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce insurance in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate of the insurance company.
On the other hand, Malus is an increase in that basic rate.
"The bonus and the malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus", explains Noguera.
After exceeding the limit of twenty-five years it makes it easier for drivers to order insurance, as the client's risk index decreases due to their experience.
For this reason, it is most recommended to arrange insurance against all risks with a discount.
"Young people are not usually able to take advantage of the experience gained in advance at the time of the accident and even in driving," says the director of the European company in Spain, adding that most of the accidents are taking place in the second year of the procedure, when the "fear of the newcomer" has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but does not have children yet, it is better to arrange insurance against all risks, if his economic situation allows.
Families with children are considered as a clientele with the lowest risk index and therefore their premiums will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with an insurance discount (which could be EUR 300) or a high bonus, extended to other participants in the operation, starting from the third year following the purchase of the vehicle.
"Its management is calmer and their purchasing capacity is higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount", notes Luis Noguera.
Pensions are recommended insurance against all risks with an insurance discount (EUR 150) or insurance extended to other participants if a high bonus has been reached.
It should be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects drivers in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a significant expenditure, which is a good reason for proper study of the insurance options that would suit us most given our personal situation.
